get blog post "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=============================================================

NAME
----

get blog post - Get a blog post from any site on the network.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Get a blog post from any site on the network.

USAGE
-----

`  <?php $blog_post = get_blog_post( $blog_id, $post_id ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$blog_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) ID of the blog.
    Default: *None*

 `$post_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) ID of the post you are looking for.
    Default: *None*

EXAMPLE
-------

From site/blog id 3, get the post with id 6.
` <?php$post_6 = get_blog_post( 3, 6 );echo $post_6->post_title;?> `

RETURNS
-------

Returns a `WP_Post` object, or `null` on failure. See `get_post` for
more information.

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_blog_post()` is located in `wp-includes/ms-functions.php`.

